adjective.description: Not carefully or skilfully finished or formed; unpolished; crude, rough.
Of an animal: newly born; not yet licked into shape; frequently (now chiefly) figurative. Hence, of a person: naive, inexperienced; unsophisticated, unrefined, uncouth.

origin: Early 17th century; earliest use found in Anthony Stafford (1586/7–c1645), author. From un- + licked.
